OL,6,FMs Powell replied: "I am pleased that
OL,7,FOwen Haggerty has now received that
OL,8,Fpardon this morning. She raised this
OL,9,Fmatter with me a couple of days ago,
OL,10,Fwhich is why I raised it with the
OL,11,FForeign Office, which is why they were
OL,12,Fin touch with her this morning."
OL,14,FShe added that the "Ministry of
OL,15,FDefence and the Foreign Office have
OL,16,Fbeen working tirelessly behind the
OL,17,Fscenes to ensure the pardon", and
OL,18,Fvowed to press them to work with Ms
OL,19,FBaxter and Mr Haggerty's family "to
OL,20,Fmake sure he comes back to the UK".
